	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">S. P.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Iam accepi literas <placeName ref="l492" cert="high">Argentina</placeName> a Burchaero.<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Der sonst in <placeName ref="l587" cert="high">Zürich</placeName> lebende englische Händler <persName ref="p505" cert="high">John Burcher</persName>, der sich offensichtlich erneut (vgl. schon <bibl>HBBW</bibl> XVIII 468, Anm. 5) aus geschäftlichen Gründen in <placeName ref="l492" cert="high">Straßburg</placeName> aufhielt.</note></s>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Is te cum tota tua familia salutat.</s>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Si placeat illuc aliquid amandare, cras habebimus nuncium<note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4">Der unbekannte, aus <placeName ref="l492" cert="high">Straßburg</placeName> kommende Überbringer von <persName ref="p505" cert="high">Burchers</persName> Brief.</note>, ut spero, certum, modo vesperi literae vestrae vicino nostro, Fabro lignario, reddantur.<pb type="edition" next="231"/></s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div2" corresp="regest2">
				<p>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Scribit <persName ref="p505" cert="high">Burcherus</persName> regem <persName ref="18500" type="auto_name">Gallorum</persName><note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6"><persName ref="p18500" cert="high">Heinrich II.</persName></note> misisse in <placeName ref="l26" cert="high">Scotiam</placeName> 5000 militum,<note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7">Siehe dazu <ref target="file13045">Nr. 2996</ref>, <ptr target="qvfn17262-2" type="qv"/>.</note> et cum his est comes quidam germanus, qui vocatur germanice Reynsgrawe, cum suis Lanskniightiis.<note xml:id="fn9" type="footnote" n="9">Zu den für <persName ref="p18500" cert="high">Heinrich II.</persName> Ende Mai angeheuerten Landsknechten s. <ref target="file12972">Nr. 2923</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17188-1" type="qv"/>; <ref target="file12973">Nr. 2924</ref>, <ptr target="qvfn17189-2" type="qv"/>. - Diese Landsknechte werden auch später noch erwähnt; s. <ref target="file13020">Nr. 2971</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17237-2" type="qv"/>; <ref target="file13043">Nr. 2994</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17260-4" type="qv"/>.<ptr target="zfnfn17279-3" type="zfn"/></note></s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Dominus det victoriam iis, qui plus student illius gloriam promovere!</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div3" corresp="regest3">
				<p>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Magna turba <placeName ref="l29" cert="high">Hispanorum</placeName>, sive colluvies nebulonum, 3 milliaribus<note xml:id="fn10" type="footnote" n="10">21 bis 25 km.</note> ab <placeName ref="l492" cert="high">Argentina</placeName> residet ac ferias<note xml:id="fn11" type="footnote" n="11">Wohl (s. oben <ptr target="qvfn17279-1" type="qv"/>) die Tage zwischen Christi Himmelfahrt und Pfingsten, die 1547 auf den 19. bzw. 29. Mai fielen.</note> agit.</s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">In quem usum Caesar<note xml:id="fn12" type="footnote" n="12"><persName ref="p18538" cert="high">Karl V.</persName></note> illorum operam applicabit, adhuc ignoratur.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div4" corresp="regest4">
				<p>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Habeo literas pro Butlaero<note xml:id="fn13" type="footnote" n="13">Der englische Geschäftsmann <persName ref="p4466" cert="high">John Butler</persName>, der damals in Konstanz lebte.</note>, qui agit <placeName ref="l457" cert="high">Constantiae</placeName>.</s>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Si quem habeas fidum, qui illuc proficiscatur, mihi significabis, rogo.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div5" corresp="regest5">
				<p>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Dominus Jesus servet te semper!</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="manual">Amen.</s>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vale bene.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tue humanitatis amantissimus, <persName ref="p1560" cert="high">Ioannes Hoperus</persName>.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Ohne Adresse.]</note>
				</p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
